F-FUSION-ATTN-MULTICTA-WALL -- round 4 of the GPU sec10 GEMM-fusion (attention) axis
=====================================================================================
2026-05-25  ubu-2  RTX 5070 sm_120 driver 580.159.03 (48 SMs)  CUDA 12.0 V12.0.140

GOAL
  Author a CORRECT, multi-CTA fused flash-attention kernel (one CTA per query block so
  the grid saturates the SMs) keeping the fusion (online softmax, S tile in shared never
  to HBM, wmma inner GEMMs), then re-time vs the cuBLAS-TC 3-launch baseline.

ROUND HISTORY
  R1 (#1013): naive-scalar fused flash-attn -> 1.4-1.5x slower (scalar inner GEMMs).
  R3 (#1039): single-warp-tile wmma fused flash-attn -> 9.4-15.5x slower AND reported
              numeric FAIL (max_rel 2.6-4.8).
  R4 (this) : multi-CTA wide-KV wmma fused flash-attn.

TWO KEY FINDINGS
  (1) The round-3 "numeric FAIL" was a METRIC ARTIFACT, not a kernel bug. The naive
      metric |err|/(|want|+1e-6) blows up on near-zero attention output elements. Under
      the honest per-row-scaled + RMS relative metric, the round-3 algorithm is already
      CORRECT (proven in clean CUDA-C nvcuda::wmma: rel_rowscale 5e-4, rms 2.6e-4, PASS
      at N=512..4096). So round 3 was actually a 9-15x SLOW correct kernel, not a broken
      one. Round 3's grid was ALSO already multi-CTA (grid=N/16) -- the deficit was that
      each CTA was 1 warp doing per-16-key serial softmax overhead, NOT a single CTA.

  (2) The round-4 lever that closes the gap: WIDEN THE KV TILE from BK=16 to BK=256
      (16 wmma key-subtiles per online-softmax round), amortizing the softmax+rescale
      overhead 16x. Measured gap closure: 9-15x -> ~2x (CUDA-C floor) / 3.4-5x (hand-PTX).

GEOMETRY SWEEP (CUDA-C oracle, MEASURED, all numeric PASS)
  - multi-warp-per-CTA (WARPS 2/4/8): SLOWER -- cuts grid count + raises smem/CTA.
  - register-resident-O: FAILED numeric (wrong m16n16k16 fp32 C-frag row map) -> dropped.
  - wide-KV single-warp (BKT 4/8/16): the winner. BKT=16 (BK=256) is the max static-smem
    feasible (BKT=32 overflows: 0xd0c0 > 0xc000).

SHIPPED KERNEL: flash_attn_wmma_mcta (hand-emit PTX, pure ASCII)
  1 warp / CTA, BQ=16 query rows, BK=256 keys/softmax round, d=64, grid=N/16.
  S(16x256 f32) + P(16x256 f16) + O(16x64 f32) all in shared; S never to HBM. Both inner
  GEMMs on wmma.mma.sync m16n16k16 (f16 mul, f32 acc). One launch.

PTXAS-CLEAN (verbatim)
  pure ASCII (0 non-ascii bytes)
  sm_80 -> rc=0  41 regs  28864 B smem  0 spill  392 B cmem
  sm_90 -> rc=0  32 regs  28864 B smem  0 spill
  driver-JIT sm_120 -> loads + runs OK
  smem 28864 B/CTA (58.7% of 49152 cap, FITS).  S+O resident in smem.

GRID OCCUPANCY: grid=N/16 -> 32 / 64 / 128 / 256 CTAs (N=512/1024/2048/4096) vs 48 SMs.

NUMERIC (hand-PTX, driver-JIT sm_120, f64 ref, honest metric) -- ALL PASS
  N=512  rel_rowscale=6.30e-4 rms=2.64e-4   N=1024 rel_rowscale=5.64e-4 rms=2.69e-4
  N=2048 rel_rowscale=6.30e-4 rms=2.73e-4   N=4096 rel_rowscale=7.14e-4 rms=2.73e-4

TIMED WALL (cuEvent 20+200 median ms, GPU clean 0% util 0 procs)
  N      fused(hand-PTX)  cuBLAS-TC   ratio    round-3   closure
  512    0.056608         0.016672    3.40x    9.4x      9.4 ->3.40x
  1024   0.114016         0.030848    3.70x    10.9x     10.9->3.70x
  2048   0.244032         0.061664    3.96x    13.3x     13.3->3.96x
  4096   0.953696         0.190272    5.01x    15.5x     15.5->5.01x
  (CUDA-C geometry floor: 1.32 / 1.44 / 1.65 / 2.04x -- the hand-PTX scalar softmax loops
   are un-vectorized, ~2-2.5x slower than nvcc's ld.shared.v4/unroll; a hexa-codegen path
   with vectorized smem loads could approach this floor.)

VERDICT: ORANGE quantified partial. CORRECT multi-CTA fused flash-attention that closes
  the round-3 wall gap by ~3-8x but does NOT beat cuBLAS-TC (still 1.3-5.0x slower). The
  GEMM-fusion (attention) axis remains NOT-won. sec10 box stays [x] only via launch-amort
  (PR #1028). At d=64 the per-tile online-softmax overhead -- not S-HBM traffic -- is the
  binding constraint; cuBLAS's huge-tile GEMM efficiency is the wall this fused path cannot
  cross with 16x16 WMMA tiles. NOT paper-eligible (paper_gate forbids ORANGE sections).

INVARIANTS
  @F f1 no LLVM.  @F f2 no C-transpile.  compiler/codegen/*.hexa UNTOUCHED (hand-emit PTX).
  The CUDA-C .cu files are correctness/geometry oracles only -- NOT the shipped fused path.
